# Warehouse Management API

A production-style inventory management system built with .NET 8 and SQL Server.

## Features

- Multi-warehouse inventory management
- Stock transfer system
- JWT Authentication & Authorization
- Transaction logging (audit system)
- Bulk data ingestion via Python
- Pagination & filtering
- Clean architecture (Controller → Service → Repository)

## Tech Stack

- .NET 8 Web API
- SQL Server (Docker)
- Entity Framework Core
- Python (Pandas, Requests)
- JWT (JSON Web Token)
- Swagger (Swashbuckle)

## Key Highlights

- Transactional consistency
- Bulk API optimization
- Audit fields (CreatedOn, LastChangedOn)
- Role-based security

## Project Structure

Controllers/      - API endpoints
Services/         - Business logic
Repositories/     - Data access layer
Data/             - DbContext
DTOs/             - Request/Response models

## Data Pipeline

CSV → Python → API → Database

## How to Run

1. Clone repo
2. Run `dotnet run`
3. Open Swagger
4. Test APIs

